{"questionId":"9842","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>An aircraft’s position is given by the coordinates (<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"z\">\n  <mi>z</mi>\n</math></span>), where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span> are the aircraft’s&nbsp;displacement east and north of an airport, and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"z\">\n  <mi>z</mi>\n</math></span> is the height of the aircraft above the ground.&nbsp;All displacements are given in kilometres.</p>\n<p>The velocity of the aircraft is given as&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  { - 150} \\\\   { - 50} \\\\   { - 20}  \\end{array}} \\right)\\,{\\text{km}}\\,{{\\text{h}}^{ - 1}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>150</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>50</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>20</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>km</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>h</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p>At 13:00 it is detected at a position 30 km east and 10 km north of the airport, and at a height&nbsp;of 5 km. Let <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> be the length of time in hours from 13:00.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down a vector equation for the displacement, <strong><em>r</em></strong> of the aircraft in terms of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\"> <mi>t</mi> </math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em><strong>r&nbsp;</strong></em><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {30} \\\\   {10} \\\\   5  \\end{array}} \\right) + t\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  { - 150} \\\\   { - 50} \\\\   { - 20}  \\end{array}} \\right)\\,\"> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mtable columnspacing=\"1em\" rowspacing=\"4pt\"> <mtr> <mtd> <mrow> <mn>30</mn> </mrow> </mtd> </mtr> <mtr> <mtd> <mrow> <mn>10</mn> </mrow> </mtd> </mtr> <mtr> <mtd> <mn>5</mn> </mtd> </mtr> </mtable> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mi>t</mi> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mtable columnspacing=\"1em\" rowspacing=\"4pt\"> <mtr> <mtd> <mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mn>150</mn> </mrow> </mtd> </mtr> <mtr> <mtd> <mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mn>50</mn> </mrow> </mtd> </mtr> <mtr> <mtd> <mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mn>20</mn> </mrow> </mtd> </mtr> </mtable> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9842","referenceCode":"SPM.2.AHL.TZ0.4a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down a vector equation for the displacement, r of the aircraft in terms of t .","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.11—Vector equation of a line in 2d and 3d"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}